{
  "stem": "1496.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "I don't know if you are aware, but we found out later on that Amon Goeth was actually selling some of the food on the black market instead to give the people food, something to eat.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "So they were trying to make money this way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1944, when the Russian army were coming closer to Poland, Schindler was ordered and all the Nazis ordered to liquidate all the concentration camp and labor camp and send the people into Germany.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time, Schindler was ordered to liquidate his factory and send all the people back to concentration camp Krakau-Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Please.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Emalia was actually the name of the factory, because Emalia in Polish is the enamel which was painted-- the pots and pans were painted with enamel.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In-- in Krakau-Plaszow, one day the Nazis announced that anybody has any foreign money, jewelry, anything has to give it up, otherwise you will be executed.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When this day came, what the Nazis did, they actual shot few people in order to scare everybody, what's going to happen to them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then the Nazis with suitcases were walking from barrack to barrack, and everybody who had any jewelry had to throw into the suitcase-- jewelry or money, whatever valuable, had to throw, watches, cameras, whatever you had.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anything what some people brought with them into the camp, they had to give it up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then what I did, I had to-- I didn't want to risk my life.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- everybody was still-- as bad as this was, everybody wanted to live, didn't want to take any chances.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I didn't want to take any chances, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- in the factory was a courtyard and Schindler built barracks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were barracks for women and men, separately.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
